{ By Reuters   Published:  19:08, 4 May 2018   https://www.dailymail.co.uk//wires/reuters/article-5692453/Capitals-sign-goalie-prospect-Samsonov-entry-level-deal.html }
The Washington Capitals have signed 2015 first-round draft pick Ilya Samsonov to an entry-level NHL deal, general manager Brian MacLellan announced on Friday. Samsonov, 21, recently finished his season with the Metallurg Magnitogorsk of Russia's Kontinental Hockey League. He posted a 2.31 goals against average and had a .926 save percentage over 26 games. The three-year deal will reportedly pay Samsonov $925,000 annually, plus potential bonuses. The Capitals didn't announce whether Samsonov would join the NHL club or its American Hockey League affiliate, the Hershey Bears. The Capitals are currently tied 2-2 in their second-round playoff series with the Pittsburgh Penguins. Braden Holtby, the current starter in Washington, went 34-16-4 this season with a 2.99 GAA and a .907 save percentage. He's improved those numbers to 2.07 and .924 in nine postseason games this postseason. --Field Level Media 
